<LG N="11" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>(11)</HEAD>
<L N="71">&para; "The hardy prikeris / vpon hors[&euml;] bak<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>The . . prikeris . . hors</I>] LR. These . . Rynners . . theyr hors H.</NOTE></L>
<L>Be sent to-forn / what ground is best to take,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Be . . toforne</I>] Bien . . afore H.</NOTE></L>
<L>In that ordynaunce, that ther be no lak<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>In that</I>] In theyr HR.</NOTE></L>
<L>Bi providance / the feelde / whan thei shal make,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>the . . shal</I>] how they the fielde shul HR.</NOTE></L>
<L N="75">An hors wole weep&euml; / for his maistir sake:<NOTE PLACE="foot">with '&para; secundum Bartholomeum de proprietatibus rerum' in margin.</NOTE></L>
