<L N="119">Whan it is grounde / hors carye it hom from melle.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>hom</I>. .] from the mylle H. <I>from</I>] <I>om</I>. L. And whan it is grounden bringeth it fro y<SUP>e</SUP> melle R.</NOTE></L>
</LG>
<LG N="18" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>(18)</HEAD>
<L N="120">&para; "In Wyntir seson / for to make bele cheere,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>bele</I>] the beal H, beal R.</NOTE></L>
<L>The hors is nedeful / wode &amp; stuff to carie;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>The hors is nedeful</I>] HR, Than is neede L. <I>stuff</I>] LH, turf R.</NOTE></L>
